<t>CREATE TABLE carbon_footprint (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  company_name STRING,
  emission_level FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id UUID,
  consumption FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE waste_management (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  company_name STRING,
  waste_type STRING,
  weight FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE eco_friendly_products (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  product_name STRING,
  price FLOAT,
  carbon_offset FLOAT
);</t><s>SELECT * FROM carbon_footprint;</s>

  product_name STRING,

  carbon_offset FLOAT
);

);

);

  device_id UUID,
  consumption FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP

  company_name STRING,
  waste_type STRING,
  weight FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE energy_consumption (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id UUID,
  consumption FLOAT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE eco_friendly_products (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  product_name STRING,
  price FLOAT,
  carbon_offset FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE carbon_footprint (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  company_name STRING,
  emission_level FLOAT
);</t><s>SELECT * FROM eco_friendly_products WHERE product_name LIKE '%organic%';</s>

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_initiatives (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_name TEXT, description TEXT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)</t><s>SELECT id, name, description FROM environmental_impact</s>

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT metric_name, actual_value FROM sustainability_metrics</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)</t><s>SELECT initiative_id, metric_id, progress_value, date_recorded FROM sustainability_progress</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)</t><s>SELECT * FROM sustainability_goals WHERE completion_date >= '2023-01-01'</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_initiatives (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_name TEXT, description TEXT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT metric_name, target_value FROM sustainability_metrics WHERE target_value < 100</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_initiatives (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_name TEXT, description TEXT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)</t><s>SELECT * FROM sustainability_initiatives WHERE start_date >= '2021-01-01'</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)</t><s>select * from sustainability_progress where progress_value < 50</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)</t><s>SELECT * FROM sustainability_progress WHERE progress_value < 50</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_initiatives (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_name TEXT, description TEXT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT * FROM environmental_impact ORDER BY name ASC</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)</t><s>select * from environmental_impact order by name asc</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_initiatives (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_name TEXT, description TEXT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)</t><s>select * from sustainability_goals order by completion_date desc</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)</t><s>select * from sustainability_metrics order by actual_value desc</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE sustainability_initiatives (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_name TEXT, description TEXT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)</t><s>SELECT * FROM sustainability_metrics ORDER BY actual_value DESC</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_initiatives (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_name TEXT, description TEXT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)</t><s>SELECT * FROM sustainability_initiatives ORDER BY start_date ASC</s>

CREATE TABLE sustainability_goals (id INT PRIMARY KEY, goal_name TEXT, target TEXT, completion_date DATE)</t><s>SELECT * FROM sustainability_progress ORDER BY date_recorded DESC</s>

CREATE TABLE environmental_impact (id INT PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, description TEXT, impact_type TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_progress (id INT PRIMARY KEY, initiative_id INT, metric_id INT, progress_value FLOAT, date_recorded DATE)

CREATE TABLE sustainability_metrics (id INT PRIMARY KEY, metric_name TEXT, description TEXT, target_value FLOAT, actual_value FLOAT)</t><s>select * from sustainability_progress order by date_recorded desc</s>
